external_knowledge:
High binding affinity indicates a strong interaction between a peptide and a protein, which is crucial in understanding protein functions and developing targeted therapies; 
In this context, "multiple peptides" implies more than one peptide is associated with a protein; 
Researcher names and protein names are used to identify specific individuals and proteins involved in the experiments.

sql:
SELECT peptide_id, MAX(logscore) AS max_logscore
FROM binding_affinities
GROUP BY peptide_id;
